title: Thirst Trap: David Tennant
body:
Thirst Trap: David Tennant

For today’s Thirst Trap installment, I’m stepping forward to pay homage to one of the longest running objects of my thirsty attentions: David Tennant. Everyone has their top 10 list… and for the better part of the last decade (Gah, I feel old) the Doctor himself has occupied the top spot for me.

1.) His Scottish Accent

2.) Those glasses… omg.

3.) That hair

4.) Those eyes

5.) Suits… and long coats.

View On WordPress

summary: you like doctor who right? who's your favorite doctor? and would you ever consider writing doctor who fanfiction?
question: you like doctor who right? who's your favorite doctor? and would you ever consider writing doctor who fanfiction?
answer:
Anon, I love Doctor Who!

Star Wars is my primary fandom right now, but before that, about three years ago, it was Doctor Who.  I’ve kept up with Doctor Who since (though I am a little behind with this season - I’ll probably catch up once the semester is over), and I really love the direction the show is going right now.

My favorite doctor is the Tenth Doctor.  What can I say?  David Tennant has such a wonderful charisma, and it translates really well into his acting.

I have written one (very short) fic for Doctor Who!  And I have a lot of old WIPs that I’m still aching to finish, somehow.  I really hope I can get back to some of them one day.

summary: What’s so exciting about the concept of The Curator is that he said that “and in years to come you might find yourself...
body: What’s so exciting about the concept of The Curator is that he said that “and in years to come you might find yourself revisiting a few, but just the old favourites.” Leaving it perfectly possible that Tennant or Smith could come back in 20-30 years to play the Curator role.. and completely destroy my soul.
